[Student "S"]
{NORTH has a nice 2\C opening hand.

With 8 points, SOUTH can make a positive response so he bids his 5-card \Hsuit.

NORTH likes \Hs, knows there are at least 33 points, but needs to make 
sure the opponents don't have two Aces so she uses Blackwood.

When SOUTH shows one Ace NORTH bids 6\H.}

